race.comment: Curries-trained DECORATIVE (4) ran his best race before spelling when narrowly beaten at Gatton. Missed a whisker here first up in stronger over 1200m and a senior rider goes on. Will position forward from the inside gate and can go one better. LINTHORPE LUCK (1) brings an easy maiden win and a CL2 placing from this track. Will give away a start but rates well and is on a quick back-up. UPSTART LOVER (9) stalked the speed but folded up badly here in a CL2. Missed a nose at Ipswich prior and that stacks right up. On a quick return and this suits better. Has to be considered. MIDNIGHT MIRACLE (7) resumed for Currie with a neck defeat at Dalby. This is harder, but she gets plenty of weight relief and is in the mix. KINDLY (10) ran well enough here last time to be around the mark.
